The Game of Life implementation is complete. The solution uses sparse representation by storing only living cells as `[x, y]` tuples in a `Set` (keyed by `"x,y"` strings), and computes the next generation by iterating only over cells adjacent to living ones — supporting the theoretically infinite grid with negative coordinates.
